  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7.</p>\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Peel and chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> over a high heat and cook for 10-15 min or until fork-tender</p>\n<p>Once cooked, drain and return them to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1857RC2602v2Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1857RC2602v2Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1857RC2602v2Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1857RC2602v2Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1857RC2602v2Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the potatoes are cooking,<strong> </strong>re-boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Dissolve 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>Knorr</strong> <strong>vegetable stock cube</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml] </span><strong><strong>boiled water</strong></strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>saffron</strong> and set aside to infuse – this is your <strong>saffron stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1857RC2602v2Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1857RC2602v2Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1857RC2602v2Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1857RC2602v2Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1857RC2602v2Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> salmon fillets</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min on each side or until browned on both sides and almost cooked through</p>\n<p>Once browned, transfer to a plate and reserve the pan (and oil)</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1857RC2602v2Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
