            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat (add a drizzle more oil if it's looking a little dry)</p>\n<p>Once hot, add 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and stir for 1 min or until a sandy paste remains</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>saffron stock</strong> with 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and <strong>clotted cream</strong> and cook for 1 min further – this is your <strong>saffron sauce</strong></p>",
